               <p>On the 20th of August, I got up in the morning about a quarter before five, and went into the yard; I heard a woman's voice in the necessary, and the prisoner came out; she said she was in liquor, and had slipped in the night before, and fell asleep on the stairs; Mr. Blair, who lives in the same house, came out; we questioned her, and let her go; when I came up stairs, I missed the things in the indictment; on the 21st of last month, I found the same person at my door, without her shoes; I took her into custody; she enquired then for a strange name; I knew her immediately, and sent for Mr. Blair, who knew her also; I never found any of my other things again, but those that were taken out of the necessary.</p>
               <p>
            
